Liquidity Risk Analysis: Consolidated Level ‚Äì LCR

The Santander Group performs the consolidated LCR ratio in the identified significant currencies, EUR, USD, GBP, BRL, MXN and CLP. On an individual basis, each of the entities also carries out its own LCR ratio in significant currency.

Units present a consistent position between the liquidity buffer and net outflows.

In the case of Latin American countries, the positions in the buffers are significantly higher in USD, with the aim of optimizing the position and ensuring high convertibility. Positions in foreign currencies are monitored in detail, carrying out, for example, currency stress scenarios.
